Establish username requirements: Establish the acceptable character set and minimum length that should be allowed for a username. For instance, usernames should be at least 6 characters long and must contain alpha-numeric characters only.



        Use whitelist validation: Whitelisting involves defining what input is acceptable. Once valid input is defined, compare all input against the established list. If the input does not match an item from the list, your application should discard it. This technique can be implemented using regular expressions. Example:
      public bool ValidateUsername(string username){    Regex rx = new Regex("(\\w|\\d){6,}");    return rx.IsMatch(username);}
